 Doug Hughes was arrested after landing his gyrocopter on the U.S. Capitol lawn to protest campaign finance laws .
After more than two years of planning , 61-year-old Doug Hughes made it through restricted airspace Wednesday carrying 535 letters -- one for each member of Congress -- and landed the aircraft on the Capitol lawn .
Hughes was promptly arrested for the stunt and charged Thursday with violating restricted airspace and operating an unregistered aircraft .